    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Ok it's only a matter of how do we update the url, here's the same widget with code fixed:\n\n``` js\nsearch.addWidget({\n  container: document.querySelector('#custom-widget'),\n  render: function(options) {\n    var link = document.createElement('a');\n    link.innerText = 'test';\n    link.addEventListener('click', function(e) {\n      e.preventDefault();\n      options.helper.toggleRefine('brand', 'Samsung');\n      history.replaceState(null, '', location.search + '&isCustom=true&test_custom=false');\n      options.helper.search();\n    });\n    this.container.innerHTML = '';\n    this.container.appendChild(link);\n  }\n});\n```\n\nSo basically, for anyone wondering, you need to do this to be able to add custom url attributes in the right way:\n\n``` js\n      options.helper.toggleRefine('brand', 'Samsung');\n      history.replaceState(null, '', location.search + '&isCustom=true&test_custom=false');\n      options.helper.search();\n```\n\nIn this particular order, using replaceState. Thanks @bobylito \n",
